Durban - Thousands of runners, their friends and families are due to arrive in Durban for the upcoming Comrades Marathon. This year 'The Ultimate Human Race' celebrates its 93rd anniversary. The marathon takes on Sunday, June 10 and is a 'down run' from Pietermaritzburg to Durban. This year is the 46th 'down run' and runners will begin their run from 5:30am outside the PMB City Hall, finishing some 12 hours later at the landmark Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban.
